    <note type="biography">
        <p>American politician and diplomat. United States senator for Louisiana, 1853–61. Appointed Confederate diplomatic commissioner to France in 1861; his detention, along with James Murray Mason, by the United States Navy in November 1861 caused a tense diplomatic situation to develop between the United States and Britain.</p></note>
